# Supabase Patterns

## Client Setup

- API/worker services use the **service role** client (bypasses RLS) — never expose this key to the frontend
- Frontend/Electron app uses the **anon key** client with user auth tokens — RLS enforces access control
- Create one Supabase client instance per service, not per request

## Queries

- Always select only the columns you need — avoid `select('*')`
- Check for errors from every Supabase call — the client does not throw, it returns `{ data, error }`

```ts
// ✅ Good
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('generations')
  .select('id, prompt, status, created_at')
  .eq('user_id', userId);

if (error) throw new DatabaseError('Failed to list generations', { cause: error });

// ❌ Bad — ignores errors
const { data } = await supabase.from('generations').select('*');
```

## Storage

- Bucket: `generation-assets` (private)
- Path pattern: `users/{user_id}/generations/{generation_id}/step_{n}/{filename}`
- Use signed URLs for frontend access — never make the bucket public
- Set short TTL on signed URLs (5-15 minutes)

## Migrations

- One migration file per logical change in `infra/supabase/migrations/`
- Never modify an existing migration that has been applied — create a new one
- Test migrations against a branch database before applying to production
